- YOUR CLAVICLE.

09:34.170 --> 09:36.468
- I'M HERE BECAUSE IT'S MY CASE.
- IT'S ALSO OUR CASE.

09:36.500 --> 09:39.230
- WE JUST SIGNED ON TO BE LEGAL
CONSULTANTS TO THE DEFENSE.

09:39.270 --> 09:40.976
SHE'S INNOCENT,
WE KNOW IT.

09:41.010 --> 09:42.409
- OH, YOU KNOW.
WELL, THAT'S GOOD.

09:42.440 --> 09:43.771
APPARENTLY YOU KNOW
MORE THAN A LEGAL SYSTEM

09:43.810 --> 09:45.300
THAT'S BEEN ESTABLISHED
FOR OVER 200 YEARS.

09:45.350 --> 09:47.671
- 200 YEARS?

09:47.720 --> 09:50.018
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW FOOLISH YOU SOUND?

09:50.050 --> 09:51.415
200, GUS.

09:51.450 --> 09:54.487
CAVEMEN WITH TIES
SUING DINOSAURS.

09:54.520 --> 09:57.023
[gruff voice]
I AM CAVEMAN.

09:57.060 --> 09:59.949
I INVENTED WHEEL, NOT CROG.
- SHAWN.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.422
- YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY BE
THIS STUPID.

10:01.460 --> 10:03.428
COME ON, DETECTIVE.

10:03.470 --> 10:04.994
-AH!

10:05.030 --> 10:08.136
- WAIT!

10:08.170 --> 10:11.298
GAH! I'M GE'I'I'ING
REALLY STRONG VIBES HERE.

10:11.340 --> 10:12.898
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
FOR THE NEXT EIGHT YEARS?

10:12.940 --> 10:15.932
BECAUSE I AM SENSING THAT
WE BECOME VERY MUCH INVOLVED.

10:15.980 --> 10:17.277
- YOU'RE WAY OFF ON THAT,
SHAWN.

10:17.310 --> 10:18.800
- DO WE HAVE UPS AND DOWNS?
- MM-HMM.

10:18.850 --> 10:20.340
- SURE, LIKE ANYONE WOULD.

10:20.380 --> 10:22.371
I CAN SEE IT SO CLEARLY.

10:22.420 --> 10:25.742
YOUR CORN-SILK HAIR NESTLED
ON THIS GENTLEMAN'S SHOULDER,

10:25.790 --> 10:27.758
RIGHT IN THE CROOK.

10:27.790 --> 10:29.553
- O'HARA, SHAKE A LEG!

10:29.590 --> 10:32.923
- NEVER HAPPENING, SHAWN.

10:32.960 --> 10:34.723
- OKAY.

10:34.760 --> 10:36.455
BUT YOU'RE ADORABLE
WHEN YOU'RE IN DENIAL.

10:36.500 --> 10:37.762
- DO NOT TALK TO HIM.

10:37.800 --> 10:40.598
- SHAWN, GUS!
THANK YOU AGAIN.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.494
OH, BUT NOW I HAVE
SO MUCH WORK TO DO.

10:42.540 --> 10:44.804
ALL THESE DEPOSITIONS AND
WITNESS REPORTS TO COMB OVER.

10:44.840 --> 10:47.434
I HAVEN'T EVEN CRACKED OPEN
THE RUBEN LEONARD FILE.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.277
CAN I COUNT ON YOUR HELP?
- SORRY, HORNSTOCK.

10:49.310 --> 10:51.244
IT'S JUST, UH,
IT'S NOT THE WAY WE WORK.

10:51.280 --> 10:53.168
I NEED TO TOUCH THINGS,
TASTE THINGS, AND SMELL THINGS.

10:53.220 --> 10:54.539
- SMELL THEM?

10:54.580 --> 10:55.945
- AND GUS DOESN'T EVEN READ.
- WHAT?

10:55.980 --> 10:59.313
- WE ALL HAVE OUR STRENGTHS.

10:59.350 --> 11:00.419
OURS ARE IN FRONT
OF THE CAMERA.

11:00.460 --> 11:02.087
[upbeat theme music]

11:02.120 --> 11:03.781
- WE'RE GOING LIVE
IN FIVE, FOUR--

11:03.830 --> 11:06.549
[mouthing numbers]

11:06.590 --> 11:08.319
[both laughing]

11:08.360 --> 11:10.499
- OKAY, WE ARE BACK,
SANTA BARBARA.

11:10.530 --> 11:13.090
AND MORTY AND I
ARE COZYING UP ON THE COUCH

11:13.140 --> 11:15.665
FOR ONE OF OUR FAMOUS
SIP N'CHAT SEGMENTS.

11:15.700 --> 11:17.133
- YOU KNOW, CONNIE, I NEVER
GET SICK OF OUR THEME MUSIC.

11:17.170 --> 11:18.933
I LOVE IT.

11:18.970 --> 11:21.734
- WELL, WE ARE JOINED TODAY
BY TWO VERY SPECIAL GUESTS.

11:21.780 --> 11:23.998
NOW THEY HAVE JUST JOINED
THE DEFENSE TEAM

11:24.050 --> 11:26.177
OF THE JACKSON HALE TRIAL.

11:26.210 --> 11:29.373
PLEASE WELCOTIA/IIAIDSHAWN SPENCER

11:29.420 --> 11:31.479
"BURTINE GUSTON."

11:31.520 --> 11:33.112
WELCOME.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.355
- THANK YOU SO MUCH,
CONNIE AND MORTY.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.278
- NOW, NOT TO BE A SKEPTIC,

11:37.330 --> 11:38.786
BUT I JUST DON'T THINK

11:38.830 --> 11:40.297
I'VE HEARD
OF A PSYCHIC DETECTIVE BEFORE.

11:40.330 --> 11:41.524
HAVE YOU, MORTY?
- NO, NO, I HAVE NOT.

11:41.560 --> 11:42.549
NO, CONNIE, NO.
- YEAH.

11:42.600 --> 11:44.227
- BUT IT SEEMS FASCINATING.

11:44.270 --> 11:46.295
- MM, FOR A CHILDREN'S PARTY
MAYBE.

11:46.330 --> 11:48.389
- WELL, YES.
- BUT FOR A MURDER TRIAL?

11:48.440 --> 11:50.408
SHAWN, I MEAN, LISTEN.

11:50.440 --> 11:53.204
SANDRA PANITCH, SHE IS FACING
SOME VERY SERIOUS CHARGES,

11:53.240 --> 11:54.673
AND I CERTAINLY
DON'T WANNA TRY HER

11:54.710 --> 11:56.405
IN THE COURT OF PUBLIC OPINION.
- NO, NO, NO, NO.

11:56.440 --> 11:57.748
- BUT I WILL SAY THIS.

11:57.780 --> 11:59.372
THINGS DO NOT
LOOK GOOD FOR HER.

11:59.410 --> 12:01.412
- NO, THEY DO NOT.
- RIGHT? OH, MY GOD.

12:01.450 --> 12:03.589
NOT TO MENTION THE SHENANIGANS
OF HER ATTORNEY.

12:03.620 --> 12:04.882
- OH, YEAH.

12:04.920 --> 12:06.649
- ADAM...
- HORNSTOCK? IS THAT IT?

12:06.690 --> 12:08.248
HORNSTOCK.
HE IS AN ODD DUCK, ISN'T HE?

12:08.290 --> 12:09.552
- YEAH.
- ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

12:09.590 --> 12:11.455
WOULDN'T YOU SAY THAT
ABOUT HIM?

12:11.490 --> 12:12.889
- YEAH, I WOULD SAY YOU TWO
HAVE YOUR WORK CUT OUT FOR YOU.

12:12.930 --> 12:14.397
[laughing]
_ UH--

12:14.430 --> 12:15.954
- WELL, DON'T WORRY,
DON'T WORRY.

12:16.000 --> 12:19.367
I WAS PRE-PRE-PRE-LAW.

12:19.400 --> 12:21.698
- AH.
OH, DOOGIE HOWSER.

12:21.740 --> 12:23.503
- [laughing]

12:23.540 --> 12:25.405
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
JACKSON HALE WAS A COLLEAGUE,

12:25.440 --> 12:27.431
BUT HE WAS ALSO A DEAR FRIEND.

12:27.480 --> 12:28.970
AND I THINK WE ALL
JUST WANT JUSTICE.

12:29.010 --> 12:30.602
- MM-HMM,
AND YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE WE WANT

12:30.650 --> 12:31.969
IS TO SEE YOU GUYS
WHEN WE COME BACK...

12:32.010 --> 12:34.478
- HEY!
- Al-TER THIS SHORT BREAK.

12:34.520 --> 12:35.839
- AND WE'RE CLEAR.
THREE MINUTES, EVERYONE.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.609
- THAT IS ONE HELL
OF A PINKIE RING.

12:37.650 --> 12:39.481
- SO...
- THANKS. THANK YOU.

12:39.520 --> 12:42.182
- SHAWN,
I WOULD GET A HUGE KICK

12:42.220 --> 12:44.757
OUT OF YOU USING
YOUR PSYCHIC POWERS

12:44.790 --> 12:49.124
TO TELL ME
WHAT I AM THINKING RIGHT NOW.

12:49.160 --> 12:50.491
- OH.

12:50.530 --> 12:52.088
- YEAH, SURE, I CAN DO THAT.

12:52.130 --> 12:53.563
THERE'S A BIT
OF PAGEANTRY INVOLVED, SO...

12:53.600 --> 12:55.329
- OH!
- I'M JUST GONNA NEED YOU TO--

12:55.370 --> 12:56.496
- I'M NOT SURPRISED.
- OKAY. TRUST THE PROCESS.

12:56.540 --> 12:57.734
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

12:57.770 --> 12:58.668
- WELL,
IT'S A PHYSICAL PROCESS.

12:58.710 --> 12:59.734
[laughs]
- MM.

12:59.770 --> 13:02.944
AND HERE IT IS.

13:02.980 --> 13:04.641
I THINK I'VE GOT IT.

13:04.680 --> 13:05.977
THE THOUGHTS THAT YOU'RE HAVING
ABOUT MY PARTNER

13:06.010 --> 13:07.875
NOT SUITABLE
FOR A MORNING SHOW.

13:10.520 --> 13:11.782
YOU KNOW, I'M GETTING
SOMETHING ELSE RIGHT NOW TOO.

13:11.820 --> 13:13.481
IT'S PRETTY JUICY.

13:13.520 --> 13:15.385
YOU GUYS AREN'T EVEN TOGETHER
RIGHT NOW.

13:15.420 --> 13:16.887
WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?
- [laughs] I DON'T THINK SO.

13:16.930 --> 13:18.557
- MORTY'S NOT EVEN STAYING
AT THE HOUSE, GUS.

13:18.590 --> 13:20.421
YEAH, HE'S CHILLING AT A MOTEL.
- REALLY?

13:20.460 --> 13:22.826
- THAT CAN'T BE GOOD, SO
YOUR RELATIONSHIP'S A SHAM THEN,

13:22.870 --> 13:25.327
WHICH MEANS THAT THIS WHOLE SHOW
IS A SHAM.

13:25.370 --> 13:26.598
- IT'S A SHAM. HEY, GET OFF!
- HEY, COME ON.

13:26.630 --> 13:27.858
- YOU GET OFF!
- MORTY, HEY!

13:27.900 --> 13:29.299
- BACK UP, BACK UP!
- MORTY, MORTY!

13:29.340 --> 13:31.331
- OW, AH!
- YEAH.

13:31.370 --> 13:33.338
- [clears throat]
60 SECONDS, EVERYONE.

13:33.380 --> 13:35.109
- COME ON, GET OVER HERE!
- MORTY.

13:35.140 --> 13:36.368
ALL RIGHT!
- STOP!

13:36.410 --> 13:37.877
- ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

13:37.910 --> 13:40.242
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU FIGURED OUT
ANY OF THAT,

13:40.280 --> 13:41.941
BUT IT IS NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

13:41.980 --> 13:44.744
- EVERYTHING IN THE PSYCHIC
REALM IS MY BUSINESS, JACK.

13:44.790 --> 13:47.679
- AND IT'S TRUE, ALL RIGHT?
OUR MARRIAGE IS ON THE BENDS.

13:47.720 --> 13:50.951
BUT THE NETWORK
TOLD US TO KEEP IT UNDER WRAPS

13:50.990 --> 13:52.457
FOR THE SAKE OF THE SHOW.

13:52.490 --> 13:54.492
- THERE IS MORE TO IT
THAN THAT.

13:54.530 --> 13:55.929
WE'RE WORKING IT OUT.
- WE REALLY ARE.

13:55.960 --> 13:57.393
- 'CAUSE I GOTTA SAY,

13:57.430 --> 13:58.920
THIS WHOLE JACKSON HALE
MURDER THING

13:58.970 --> 14:01.837
HAS JUST REALLY MADE ME
APPRECIATE THE FRAILTY OF LIFE.

14:01.870 --> 14:03.804
I MEAN, HE IS OUT THERE
GALLIVANTING AROUND

14:03.840 --> 14:05.364
WITH ALL THESE WOMEN...

14:05.410 --> 14:06.934
- I WARNED HIM.
- IT GETS HIM KILLED.

14:06.980 --> 14:08.004
[whispering]
IT GETS HIM KILLED.

14:08.040 --> 14:09.803
ALSO, I DON'T MIND SAYING,

14:09.840 --> 14:11.444
BEING SINGLE II/INWTHIS TOWN...

14:11.480 --> 14:13.619
- IS WORSE THAN DEATH,
YOU KNOW?

14:13.650 --> 14:15.675
AND I HAVE STARTED
TO COME TO REALIZE

14:15.720 --> 14:18.382
VERY, VERY, VERY RECENTLY

14:18.420 --> 14:22.208
THAT I HAVE A MAN
RIGHT NEXT TO ME.

14:22.260 --> 14:25.957
AND HE IS JUST FINE.
- HEY, LOOK.

14:25.990 --> 14:29.596
I MEAN, I KNOW I'M A REALLY
GOOD-LOOKING NEWSCASTER,

14:29.630 --> 14:31.769
AND I COULD AARON ECKHART
MY WAY AROUND TOWN IF I WANTED--

14:31.800 --> 14:34.064
- AARON ECKHART?
- WELL, WHATEVER.

14:34.100 --> 14:36.136
I CAN JIM CAVIEZEL MY WAY
AROUND TOWN IF I WANT.

14:36.170 --> 14:38.934
- WE WOULD JUST APPRECIATE IF
YOU WOULD KEEP THIS UNDER WRAPS.

14:38.970 --> 14:40.506
- PLEASE, FOR THE SAKE
OF THE CREW MORALE.

14:40.540 --> 14:42.201
- WHAT?
- I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

14:42.240 --> 14:43.605
MS. CAMP, YOUR TENNIS LESSON
WAS CHANGED TO 5:00 PM. TODAY.

14:43.650 --> 14:45.174
- THANK YOU, PRISCILLA.

14:45.210 --> 14:46.643
- MR. SPENCER...
- THAT'S ME.

14:46.680 --> 14:49.843
- AND FRIEND,
I'M PRISCILLA MORGENSTERN.

14:49.880 --> 14:51.689
I'M THE RECEPTIONIST HERE.

14:51.720 --> 14:54.154
I WAS TOLD THAT YOU WOULD LIKE
A TOUR OF THE STUDIO.

14:54.190 --> 14:55.657
- WELL, IF YOU ARE THE STUDIO,
THEN YES, THAT'S CORRECT.

14:55.690 --> 14:57.328
- AND THEN WE'D LIKE TO SEE

14:57.360 --> 14:59.681
WHERE THIS HORRIBLE MURDER
TOOK PLACE.

14:59.730 --> 15:01.254
- ALL RIGHT,
LET'S WALK THE CRIME.

15:01.300 --> 15:03.029
- YOU'RE STANDING
EXACTLY RIGHT WHERE IT HAPPENED.

15:03.070 --> 15:04.469
[whispering] SO GRISLY.
- ALL RIGHT, PRISCILLA.

15:04.500 --> 15:05.990
WHAT AM I LOOKING AT?
WHAT IS THIS?

15:06.030 --> 15:09.090
- THIS IS A GREEN SCREEN,
SO WE CAN SUPERIMPOSE

15:09.140 --> 15:11.199
ANY IMAGES OF THE WEATHER
WE WOULD LIKE ONTO IT.

15:11.240 --> 15:13.401
- HE WOULD BRING A GIRL BACK
TO WHERE HE DOES THE WEATHER?

15:13.440 --> 15:14.907
WAS THIS A TYPICAL FRIDAY NIGHT
FOR HIM?

15:14.940 --> 15:17.147
- I DIDN'T REALLY
KNOW HIM ENOUGH TO SAY.

15:17.180 --> 15:21.116
RUMOR HAS IT HE WAS
INTO SOME PRETTY KINKY STUFF.

15:21.150 --> 15:24.039
I GUESS SOME GIRLS
LIKE A WEATHER SET AND A CAMERA.

15:24.090 --> 15:26.650
- GUS DOES THE SAME THING, BUT
HE'S THE ONLY ONE IN THE VIDEOS.

15:26.690 --> 15:28.555
- MY TYPICAL FRIDAY NIGHT
IS ALONE ON MY COUCH

15:28.590 --> 15:31.423
EATING LEI-TOVER SHISHITO PEPPERS
AND WATCHING JERICHO.

15:31.460 --> 15:33.951
- REALLY?
- FOLLOW ME.

15:34.000 --> 15:35.399
- GUESS THERE'S A LID
FOR EVERY POT.

15:35.430 --> 15:37.159
- YEAH.

15:37.200 --> 15:38.667
- THIS IS WHERE WE KEEP
ALL OUR NEWSCASTERS' OFFICES,

15:38.700 --> 15:40.395
OUR EDITING BAYS ALSO.

15:40.440 --> 15:42.738
SEVERAL NOTICES FOR CAT-SITTERS
IF YOU NEED ANY.

15:42.770 --> 15:44.658
- HEY, HO, HO!

15:44.710 --> 15:46.701
THIS HERE IS THE BREAK ROOM?

15:46.740 --> 15:47.729
- ARE THOSE SNACKS?
- MAY WE PARTAKE?

15:47.780 --> 15:48.974
- ARE THEY FREE?
I CALL IT FIRST.

15:49.010 --> 15:49.829
- JUST NEED A LITTLE SOMETHING
TO HOLD ME OVER.

15:49.880 --> 15:51.939
- VISITORS DON'T GET SNACKS.

15:51.980 --> 15:53.709
THIS ALSO DOUBLES
AS RUBEN LEONARD'S OFFICE.

15:53.750 --> 15:55.911
HE IS OUR ROVING
HUMAN INTEREST REPORTER.

15:55.950 --> 15:57.884
- OH.
- ALTHOUGH MOST OF HIS STORIES

15:57.920 --> 16:00.150
ARE USUALLY NEITHER
OF THOSE THINGS.

16:00.190 --> 16:03.580
RUBEN IS TAKING OVER
AS OUR TEMPORARY WEATHERMAN.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.757
- I HAVEN'T EVEN CRACKED OPEN
THE RUBEN LEONARD FILE.

16:05.790 --> 16:08.657
- PRISCILLA, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE RUBEN IS ROVING

16:08.700 --> 16:11.089
AT THIS VERY MOMENT?

16:13.000 --> 16:15.560
GUS, THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE

16:15.600 --> 16:17.739
TO WALK ON THE MOON
IF THE MOON WAS BLACK.

16:17.770 --> 16:19.738
- THE MOON IS BLACK, SHAWN.
- WHAT?

16:19.770 --> 16:21.408
- THE MOON IS BLACK,
AEGEUS IS BLACK,

16:21.440 --> 16:23.169
AND GRIMACE IS BLACK.
END OF STORY.

16:23.210 --> 16:25.849
- WHOA, GUS!
I THINK THAT'S RUBEN LEONARD.

16:25.880 --> 16:27.370
- IS HE DEAD?
- I DON'T KNOW.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.911
RUBEN?

16:29.950 --> 16:32.612
RUBEN!

16:32.650 --> 16:34.083
RUBEN!

16:34.120 --> 16:36.213
[both shout]

16:37.330 --> 16:38.786
RUBEN!
RUBEN LEONARD!

16:38.830 --> 16:41.424
- [groaning]
- HE'S ALIVE, HE'S ALIVE!

16:41.460 --> 16:44.429
- HOO!

16:44.470 --> 16:46.324
I'M GOOD.
I'M GOOD.

16:46.370 --> 16:47.689
I JUST HAVE A SCOLIOSIS ROD
IN MY BACK,

16:47.740 --> 16:49.867
SO UNEVEN SURFACES
ARE NOT MY FRIEND.

16:49.900 --> 16:52.232
- OH, OKAY.
I SEE.

16:52.270 --> 16:53.976
WELL...

16:54.010 --> 16:55.773
MY NAME IS SHAWN SPENCER.
I AM A PSYCHIC DETECTIVE.

16:55.810 --> 16:58.142
THIS IS GUS.
HE'S MY BLACK CAMERON.

16:58.180 --> 16:59.670
WE ARE LEGAL CONSULTANTS

16:59.710 --> 17:01.371
ON THE JACKSON HALE
MURDER TRIAL.

17:01.420 --> 17:02.739
- WE'D LIKE TO ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

17:02.780 --> 17:04.645
- OH, UH, I'M ABOUT TO GO
ON THE AIR LIVE,

17:04.690 --> 17:06.112
AND I NEED TO PRACTICE THIS,

17:06.150 --> 17:07.811
SO I DON'T LOOK LIKE
A COMPLETE IDIOT.

17:07.860 --> 17:08.884
- DO YOU HAVE UNTIL 2007?

17:08.920 --> 17:10.626
[Shawn and Gus laughing]

17:10.660 --> 17:14.152
- WHAT WAS YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH JACKSON HALE?

17:14.200 --> 17:16.327
- I ADMIRED HIM GREATLY.

17:20.700 --> 17:22.634
- BUT ISN'T IT TRUE
THAT YOU TOO

17:22.670 --> 17:24.809
WANTED TO BE A WEATHERMAN?

17:24.840 --> 17:26.865
OH, I LOVE THE WEATHER, BUT I
COULD NEVER DO WHAT HE DID.

17:26.910 --> 17:29.003
- SO YOU REALLY ENJOY
GETTING UP AT 4:00 AM.

17:29.040 --> 17:31.838
AND COVERING GOLETA SENIORS'
BAKEOFF AND POETRY JAM?

17:31.880 --> 17:33.677
- YOU KNOW, I DO,
BUT WHAT CAN I SAY?

17:33.720 --> 17:36.018
I'M A FAN OF THE ARTS.
- RUBEN?

17:36.050 --> 17:36.971
WE'RE READY.
- OKAY.

17:37.020 --> 17:38.749
- GUS.

17:38.790 --> 17:40.712
WE GOT THIS GUY.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.284
- HELLO, I'M RUBEN LEONARD,

17:42.320 --> 17:44.584
AND ALL THESE KIDS
ARE JUMPING FOR CHARITY.

17:44.630 --> 17:45.654
OH!

17:45.690 --> 17:47.157
both: OH!
- BOY!

17:47.200 --> 17:48.724
CONNIE, DID YOU SEE
THAT DIRECT HIT?

17:48.760 --> 17:49.988
- OOH!

17:50.030 --> 17:52.362
- [groans]

17:58.010 --> 17:59.898
- YOUR WITNESS,
MR. HORNSTOCK.

17:59.940 --> 18:01.373
- LET'S GO.

18:01.410 --> 18:05.346
- YOU GOING TO QUESTION HIM
OR NOT?

18:05.380 --> 18:07.348
- OH, SHAWN, MY FATHER'S HERE.
HE'S COME TO WATCH ME FAIL.

18:07.380 --> 18:08.779
- HUH?

18:08.820 --> 18:10.071
- WAIT, YOU DON'T THINK
RUBEN LEONARD

18:10.120 --> 18:11.519
HAD ANYTHING TO DO
WITH THE MURDER, DO YOU?

18:11.550 --> 18:12.915
- NOT REALLY, NO.

18:12.950 --> 18:14.656
BUT IF WE CAN GET ONE MEMBER
OF THAT JURY

18:14.690 --> 18:16.009
TO ASK THE SAME QUESTION,
WE'RE IN BUSINESS.

18:16.060 --> 18:17.425
START WITH THIS.

18:17.460 --> 18:18.927
- MR. LEONARD,

18:18.960 --> 18:21.155
YOU ARE A METEOROLOGIST,
AREN'T YOU?

18:21.200 --> 18:24.920
- I AM INDEED.
- BUT NOT ON THE AIR.

18:24.970 --> 18:25.994
- NO, NOT THUS FAR.

18:26.030 --> 18:28.737
- WELL, MAYBE THAT'S BECAUSE...

18:28.770 --> 18:31.068
YOU DON'T HAVE
A METEOROLOGIST'S NAME.

18:31.110 --> 18:33.203
- I DON'T FOLLOW.

18:33.240 --> 18:35.003
- WELL, IF I WAS TO LOOK UP
THE NAME LEONARD

18:35.040 --> 18:36.439
IN, SAY, A WEATHER GLOSSARY,

18:36.480 --> 18:38.300
WOULD I SEE A DEFINITION?

18:38.350 --> 18:41.171
- NO, YOU WOULDN'T.
WHERE IS THIS GOING?

18:41.220 --> 18:43.074
- YES, MR. HORNSTOCK,
WHERE IS THIS GOING?

18:43.120 --> 18:44.917
- OH, I'M SORRY,
YOUR HONOR,

18:44.950 --> 18:47.418
IT'S JUST THAT EVERY SUCCESSFUL
WEATHERMAN THAT I KNOW

18:47.460 --> 18:49.189
HAS A REAL WEATHERMAN'S NAME.

18:49.220 --> 18:51.586
JACKSON HALE, FOR EXAMPLE.

18:51.630 --> 18:52.824
- THAT ISN'T EVEN
HIS REAL NAME.

18:52.860 --> 18:54.225
- PRECISELY!

18:54.260 --> 18:55.750
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED
